theorem interior_closure_interClosure_subset_interior_closure_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∩ closure B)) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
  -- `A ∩ closure B` is contained in `closure B`.
  have h : A ∩ closure B ⊆ closure B := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.2
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h_closure : closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ closure B := closure_mono h
  -- Applying `interior_mono` yields the desired inclusion.
  exact interior_mono h_closure

theorem closure_inter_closure_subset_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hB : IsClosed B) :
    closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ B := by
  -- Since `B` is closed, its closure is itself.
  have h_closure_eq : closure B = B := hB.closure_eq
  -- First, establish the inclusion before taking closures.
  have h_subset : A ∩ closure B ⊆ B := by
    intro x hx
    -- `hx.2 : x ∈ closure B`, rewrite using `h_closure_eq`.
    simpa [h_closure_eq] using hx.2
  -- Apply `closure_mono` and rewrite once more with `h_closure_eq`.
  have h_closure : closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ closure B := closure_mono h_subset
  simpa [h_closure_eq] using h_closure

theorem interior_closure_interClosure_subset_interior_closure_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∩ closure B)) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
  -- First, observe the basic set-inclusion.
  have h₁ : A ∩ closure B ⊆ closure B := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.2
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h₂ : closure (A ∩ closure B) ⊆ closure B := closure_mono h₁
  -- Finally, monotonicity of `interior` gives the desired result.
  exact interior_mono h₂

theorem closure_interInterior_subset_inter_closure'
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A ∩ interior B) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- `A ∩ interior B` is contained in `A`.
  have hxA : x ∈ closure A := by
    have hSub : A ∩ interior B ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    exact (closure_mono hSub) hx
  -- `A ∩ interior B` is also contained in `B` (because `interior B ⊆ B`).
  have hxB : x ∈ closure B := by
    have hSub : A ∩ interior B ⊆ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact (interior_subset : interior B ⊆ B) hy.2
    exact (closure_mono hSub) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB
